WEBVTT

NOTE Paragraph

00:00:00.360 --> 00:00:01.370
Before I begin,

00:00:01.370 --> 00:00:02.860
I need to warn people that

00:00:02.860 --> 00:00:04.270
this is a really dark topic,

00:00:04.270 --> 00:00:05.890
and the things I've uncovered were

00:00:05.890 --> 00:00:07.380
difficult for me to deal with,

00:00:07.380 --> 00:00:10.230
so I can only reasonably expect
them to be difficult for you too.

00:00:10.610 --> 00:00:11.860
It's also worth mentioning that,

00:00:11.860 --> 00:00:13.140
unless I said otherwise,

00:00:13.140 --> 00:00:15.710
I'm going to be using fictional
names and usernames.

00:00:17.140 --> 00:00:17.820
Okay.

00:00:18.250 --> 00:00:18.960
So...

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:20.370
For me, this whole thing

00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:21.910
started just before Christmas.

00:00:22.330 --> 00:00:23.830
As regular viewers know,

00:00:23.830 --> 00:00:25.840
I run a few teams
who develop software

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:27.510
that helps people write music.

00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:30.510
And in order to make sure that
our software is working as expected,

00:00:30.510 --> 00:00:32.260
we're always on the
lookout for music people

00:00:32.260 --> 00:00:33.610
who write using our tools.

00:00:34.040 --> 00:00:34.930
So, recently,

00:00:34.930 --> 00:00:35.940
a friend I work with

00:00:35.940 --> 00:00:37.260
stumbled across a composer

00:00:37.260 --> 00:00:38.290
I'm going to call

00:00:38.290 --> 00:00:39.360
'Bobby C',

00:00:39.360 --> 00:00:41.090
who'd been sharing music on YouTube

00:00:41.090 --> 00:00:42.750
that he'd made using our software.

00:00:43.030 --> 00:00:45.470
And as my friend looked
through Bobby C's work,

00:00:45.470 --> 00:00:47.810
he discovered a
really unnerving upload

00:00:47.810 --> 00:00:49.390
that had come out
just the day before,

00:00:49.390 --> 00:00:50.170
titled:

00:00:50.170 --> 00:00:51.610
"My final piece".

00:00:51.880 --> 00:00:53.520
My friend also noticed
another upload

00:00:53.520 --> 00:00:55.110
which came out at the same time.

00:00:55.430 --> 00:00:56.600
It was a final goodbye

00:00:56.600 --> 00:00:58.460
from Bobby C to all his subscribers.

00:00:58.700 --> 00:01:00.320
He thanked them for
all the kind words

00:01:00.320 --> 00:01:01.790
they said about his music,

00:01:01.790 --> 00:01:03.500
thanked them for subscribing to him,

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:05.670
and then, very
matter-of-factly, announced

00:01:05.670 --> 00:01:07.070
that he was ending his life.

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:08.360
And then that was it.

00:01:08.960 --> 00:01:10.800
My friend was very alarmed by this.

00:01:11.070 --> 00:01:13.250
These two videos
weren't yet 24 hours old

00:01:13.250 --> 00:01:14.500
by the time he'd found them,

00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:15.970
so he acted quickly,

00:01:15.970 --> 00:01:18.200
trying to track down
Bobby C on social media

00:01:18.200 --> 00:01:20.180
to find a way to get
a message to him.

00:01:20.180 --> 00:01:21.310
He then sent me a message

00:01:21.310 --> 00:01:22.850
to let me know what was happening.

00:01:23.150 --> 00:01:24.590
So, after some searching, my friend

00:01:24.590 --> 00:01:27.210
eventually tracked down
a post onto a different alias

00:01:27.210 --> 00:01:29.910
on a forum that was dedicated
to the subject of s---cide.

00:01:30.210 --> 00:01:32.040
This post was only a few hours old.

00:01:32.290 --> 00:01:33.150
It was titled:

00:01:33.150 --> 00:01:34.340
"I'm ready to do it..."

00:01:34.660 --> 00:01:35.400
In the post,

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:37.600
the user identified
himself as Bobby C,

00:01:37.600 --> 00:01:40.440
and then described the method
he was going to use to end his life.

00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:42.020
In response to this post

00:01:42.020 --> 00:01:43.960
were a few replies
bidding him farewell

00:01:43.960 --> 00:01:45.930
and complimenting
him on his bravery.

00:01:45.930 --> 00:01:47.140
Now, as you can imagine,

00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:48.890
this got my friend
into quite a panic.

00:01:49.150 --> 00:01:51.690
He began frantically searching
to find out more information.

00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:52.920
Eventually,

00:01:52.920 --> 00:01:54.630
we discovered what
country he was from,

00:01:54.630 --> 00:01:56.340
and with a little bit more work,

00:01:56.340 --> 00:01:57.820
discovered his real name too.

00:01:57.820 --> 00:01:59.900
We passed this information
to local authorities,

00:01:59.900 --> 00:02:01.700
but unfortunately it was too late.

00:02:02.200 --> 00:02:04.060
We got confirmation that Bobby C,

00:02:04.060 --> 00:02:05.650
who's actually a young teenager,

00:02:05.650 --> 00:02:06.880
had ended his life in

00:02:06.880 --> 00:02:08.480
an incredibly shocking way.

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:11.040
We were obviously really
distraught by this.

00:02:11.040 --> 00:02:13.100
For us, it happened over
the matter of a few hours,

00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:14.670
and we didn't know
how to process it.

00:02:15.180 --> 00:02:16.120
Anyway, a little later

00:02:16.120 --> 00:02:18.330
after we'd received
confirmation of his passing,

00:02:18.330 --> 00:02:20.540
I went for a walk with
my kids to a local park,

00:02:20.850 --> 00:02:22.330
and a thought began to nag me.

00:02:22.800 --> 00:02:23.580
"Bobby C."

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:24.660
"You know what?"

00:02:24.660 --> 00:02:25.840
"I think I know that name."

00:02:26.150 --> 00:02:27.080
So when I got back home,

00:02:27.080 --> 00:02:29.420
I searched for him on
various social media channels,

00:02:29.420 --> 00:02:31.050
and immediately he popped up.

00:02:31.460 --> 00:02:33.750
Turns out he followed me in
quite a few different places.

00:02:34.120 --> 00:02:35.780
He'd commented on
a few of my posts,

00:02:35.780 --> 00:02:38.700
and had been a reasonably active
member of my Discord server,

00:02:38.700 --> 00:02:41.300
which is a place where
people largely discuss music.

00:02:41.690 --> 00:02:43.900
He was interested in composing
more than anything else.

00:02:44.130 --> 00:02:46.110
He'd helped other composers
with their pieces,

00:02:46.110 --> 00:02:47.780
and showcased his music one time

00:02:47.780 --> 00:02:49.130
on one of the listening sessions.

00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:51.160
Like me, he was a fan of chess,

00:02:51.160 --> 00:02:52.690
and he seemed to have a
pretty solid knowledge

00:02:52.690 --> 00:02:53.910
of the standard openings.

00:02:54.340 --> 00:02:56.880
He also took part in some of
the sillier activities too,

00:02:56.880 --> 00:02:57.430
like

00:02:57.430 --> 00:02:58.760
submitting fun images of

00:02:58.760 --> 00:03:01.900
really janky-looking musical toys
he'd found in his local store.

00:03:02.240 --> 00:03:04.600
He found it funny one time when
I referred to my kids as

00:03:04.600 --> 00:03:05.550
"janklings"

00:03:05.550 --> 00:03:07.580
because one night they
just wouldn't go to sleep.

00:03:07.990 --> 00:03:09.420
Looking back over his messages,

00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:11.370
he just seemed like a
really fun sweet kid.

00:03:11.680 --> 00:03:12.580
And with more digging,

00:03:12.580 --> 00:03:14.200
we got a better glimpse
into his life.

00:03:14.200 --> 00:03:16.980
We found out more about his
hobbies and academic achievements.

00:03:16.980 --> 00:03:18.600
We found out about his school,

00:03:18.600 --> 00:03:20.840
as well as the wider
community he was active in.

00:03:21.250 --> 00:03:23.920
Seeing the impact his death
had on that community was-

00:03:23.920 --> 00:03:25.150
was just horrible.

00:03:25.150 --> 00:03:26.700
The- There's no other word for it.

00:03:26.700 --> 00:03:28.930
Now, there was another reason
I did so much digging

00:03:28.930 --> 00:03:30.770
into his activity on my Discord,

00:03:30.770 --> 00:03:32.080
which is that I wanted
to see whether

00:03:32.080 --> 00:03:34.520
he'd ever hinted at his
intentions to anyone there.

00:03:34.850 --> 00:03:35.450
Turns out,

00:03:35.770 --> 00:03:36.410
no.

00:03:36.410 --> 00:03:37.030
Nothing.

00:03:37.030 --> 00:03:39.690
Not once did he say anything
even remotely pessimistic.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:41.840
He encouraged other users
with their music

00:03:41.840 --> 00:03:42.480
and

00:03:42.480 --> 00:03:44.370
took part in all the
goofiness that goes on.

00:03:44.660 --> 00:03:46.390
So, I felt, like, some relief

00:03:46.390 --> 00:03:47.670
that we didn't miss anything.

00:03:47.840 --> 00:03:49.960
He'd never said a word
about his problems to us.

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:51.670
But then I began to wonder,

00:03:51.670 --> 00:03:52.270
"Why?"

00:03:52.270 --> 00:03:54.220
Like, why did he tell
this other group instead?

00:03:54.220 --> 00:03:55.690
And that's when I began
to take a closer look

00:03:55.690 --> 00:03:57.340
at the forum I mentioned earlier,

00:03:57.340 --> 00:03:59.430
the place where he posted
his final farewell.

00:03:59.880 --> 00:04:02.440
Now, guidelines for media
reporting on this subject

00:04:02.440 --> 00:04:05.080
strongly discourages
naming this site directly.

00:04:05.390 --> 00:04:07.060
For this reason, I'm
gonna call the site

00:04:07.060 --> 00:04:08.150
'Sorrow Solution',

00:04:08.150 --> 00:04:09.830
or 'SS' for short.

00:04:10.140 --> 00:04:12.510
KELLI: Well, I was put in touch
with someone from the AFSP,

00:04:12.510 --> 00:04:14.670
which is the American Foundation
for S---cide Prevention.

00:04:14.670 --> 00:04:15.520
Um...

00:04:15.520 --> 00:04:17.630
This was early back in 2020,

00:04:17.630 --> 00:04:18.400
and...

00:04:18.400 --> 00:04:19.180
and I asked her,

00:04:19.180 --> 00:04:20.550
"Did you get a chance
to look at this?"

00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:21.560
And she said, "I-"

00:04:21.560 --> 00:04:22.450
"I can't even look at it."

00:04:22.450 --> 00:04:23.430
"It's so bad."

00:04:23.990 --> 00:04:24.950
"I can't even look at it."

00:04:24.950 --> 00:04:25.760
And- And so...

00:04:25.760 --> 00:04:26.850
MARTIN (narrating): This is Kelli.

00:04:26.850 --> 00:04:28.440
She got in contact
with me after reading

00:04:28.440 --> 00:04:30.910
some objections I posted
on the SS forum.

00:04:31.370 --> 00:04:32.540
Her son took his own life

00:04:32.540 --> 00:04:34.990
after being coached
by this site in 2020.

00:04:35.210 --> 00:04:35.950
Since then,

00:04:35.950 --> 00:04:38.430
she's been campaigning in
the U.S. to have it shut down.

00:04:38.430 --> 00:04:40.160
MARTIN: How have you
and your family coped,

00:04:40.160 --> 00:04:41.890
given that you know
about this forum

00:04:41.890 --> 00:04:43.970
and you know that this
forum was involved?

00:04:44.560 --> 00:04:45.740
KELLI: I mean, it's

00:04:45.740 --> 00:04:46.600
a nightmare.

00:04:47.310 --> 00:04:48.220
It's a nightmare

00:04:48.220 --> 00:04:49.590
and it's something that,

00:04:50.280 --> 00:04:51.510
uh, you know, is...

00:04:52.160 --> 00:04:53.840
my family doesn't want me to do,

00:04:54.180 --> 00:04:56.320
because obviously
it's very unhealthy.

00:04:56.710 --> 00:04:57.870
Um, it's...

00:04:57.870 --> 00:05:00.160
You know, when you're
staring at a s---cide website

00:05:00.160 --> 00:05:02.140
for 12 to 18 hours a day,

00:05:03.170 --> 00:05:04.400
trying to get information,

00:05:04.400 --> 00:05:05.660
you know, for The New York Times,

00:05:05.660 --> 00:05:07.350
trying to put parts
of pieces together

00:05:07.350 --> 00:05:09.000
and trying to figure out who's who,

00:05:09.290 --> 00:05:11.500
what is what, what is
going on, who was involved,

00:05:11.500 --> 00:05:12.180
you know?

00:05:13.320 --> 00:05:14.840
And while you're trying to grieve

00:05:15.080 --> 00:05:16.520
and- and wrap your head around,

00:05:16.520 --> 00:05:17.870
you know, the loss of your...

00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:20.660
child that you- you
will never see again.

00:05:20.910 --> 00:05:22.290
It's... horrific.

00:05:22.720 --> 00:05:24.410
It's- I mean, there
really are no words

00:05:24.410 --> 00:05:25.340
to describe

00:05:25.340 --> 00:05:26.300
what it's done.

00:05:26.570 --> 00:05:28.430
MARTIN (narrating):
Kelli introduced me
to other parents

00:05:28.430 --> 00:05:30.060
whose children have
also taken their lives

00:05:30.060 --> 00:05:31.670
after exposure to SS,

00:05:31.670 --> 00:05:33.990
and who are now also campaigning
in their own countries.

00:05:34.210 --> 00:05:35.860
It was learning about
their difficulties

00:05:35.860 --> 00:05:37.590
in raising awareness
about this site

00:05:37.590 --> 00:05:39.110
and in getting it shut down

00:05:39.110 --> 00:05:40.660
that convinced me
to become involved.

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:42.960
We'll speak to some
of these parents later,

00:05:42.960 --> 00:05:45.660
as well as legislators
in the U.K. and the U.S..

00:05:46.380 --> 00:05:48.460
The purpose of this
video is twofold.

00:05:48.460 --> 00:05:50.300
First, I want to draw
people's attention

00:05:50.300 --> 00:05:52.880
to the criminal nature
of this specific forum

00:05:52.880 --> 00:05:54.400
to warn them of its dangers.

00:05:54.640 --> 00:05:55.690
I guarantee you,

00:05:55.690 --> 00:05:57.430
if you've not encountered
this place before,

00:05:57.430 --> 00:05:59.360
you won't believe how
bad it actually is.

00:05:59.810 --> 00:06:01.750
Now, my second reason
is to do something

00:06:01.750 --> 00:06:03.950
I've not really seen in
any other media coverage.

00:06:04.220 --> 00:06:06.750
Since SS gets millions
of page views a month,

00:06:07.070 --> 00:06:09.560
(it had 10 million views
in September 2022)

00:06:09.840 --> 00:06:10.880
it has a lot of users,

00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:12.780
and I want to address them directly.

00:06:12.780 --> 00:06:14.560
If you're a user of this site.

00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:16.870
I believe there are
overwhelmingly strong reasons

00:06:16.870 --> 00:06:18.190
why you should leave it.

00:06:18.190 --> 00:06:19.640
I believe you are being used

00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:22.210
to contribute to a significant
level of destruction.

00:06:22.210 --> 00:06:24.200
Destruction you have
not been informed about.

00:06:24.530 --> 00:06:25.520
So let's get started.

00:06:26.040 --> 00:06:27.900
The SS forum exclusively deals with

00:06:27.900 --> 00:06:29.910
matters relating to
ending one's life.

00:06:30.200 --> 00:06:32.560
At first glance, it's a little
tricky to find your bearings

00:06:32.560 --> 00:06:35.140
due to all the specialized
jargon and abbreviations.

00:06:35.650 --> 00:06:36.480
For example,

00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:39.440
the act of bringing one's life
to an end is referred to as

00:06:39.440 --> 00:06:40.470
'CTB'.

00:06:40.470 --> 00:06:41.630
which stands for either

00:06:41.630 --> 00:06:42.598
'cease to breathe'

00:06:42.600 --> 00:06:43.640
or, more popularly,

00:06:43.640 --> 00:06:44.740
'catch the bus'.

00:06:45.050 --> 00:06:46.030
So, while thrawling the site,

00:06:46.030 --> 00:06:48.260
you'll immediately be
confronted with posts like:

00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:49.870
"Preferred method of CTB?"

00:06:49.870 --> 00:06:50.400
or:

00:06:50.400 --> 00:06:51.080
"Please help!"

00:06:51.080 --> 00:06:52.460
Wanna CTB by

00:06:52.460 --> 00:06:53.510
[name of method]

00:06:53.510 --> 00:06:54.940
by [sic] worried about SI".

00:06:55.320 --> 00:06:56.370
'SI' stands for

00:06:56.370 --> 00:06:57.950
'survival instinct', by the way.

00:06:58.200 --> 00:06:59.750
And when diving into these posts,

00:06:59.750 --> 00:07:01.160
the first thing you'll
observe is just

00:07:01.160 --> 00:07:02.970
the absence of content moderation,

00:07:02.970 --> 00:07:04.780
despite the site's main rule:

00:07:05.170 --> 00:07:06.380
"Do not encourage,"

00:07:06.380 --> 00:07:07.170
"suggest,"

00:07:07.170 --> 00:07:07.900
"manipulate,"

00:07:07.900 --> 00:07:08.490
"coerce,"

00:07:08.490 --> 00:07:09.670
"or help users carry out"

00:07:09.670 --> 00:07:11.370
"acts of any nature whatsoever,"

00:07:11.370 --> 00:07:12.590
"including CTB."

00:07:12.770 --> 00:07:15.640
"Only provide factual information and emotional support"

00:07:15.640 --> 00:07:16.870
"to those who ask for it."

00:07:17.080 --> 00:07:19.170
This rule is a complete smokescreen.

00:07:19.170 --> 00:07:21.490
All you need to do is
click on almost any post

00:07:21.490 --> 00:07:23.120
and you'll immediately find users

00:07:23.120 --> 00:07:24.350
blatantly breaking it.

00:07:24.350 --> 00:07:25.160
For example,

00:07:25.160 --> 00:07:26.260
in a post titled:

00:07:26.260 --> 00:07:28.050
"I need to CTB tomorrow",

00:07:28.050 --> 00:07:28.950
the user says:

00:07:28.950 --> 00:07:30.310
"Please help me with a way out."

00:07:30.310 --> 00:07:32.190
"My preferred method
has a low success rate"

00:07:32.190 --> 00:07:33.660
"and I can't think of anything else."

00:07:34.020 --> 00:07:35.310
The first response to this

00:07:35.310 --> 00:07:37.700
is advice so specific and so graphic

00:07:37.700 --> 00:07:39.190
I couldn't possibly repeat it here.

00:07:39.580 --> 00:07:42.730
This is a standard example of
daily conversation on this forum.

00:07:42.730 --> 00:07:44.970
The people who run this
server also actively

00:07:44.970 --> 00:07:47.400
discourage advice that
tells people to seek help.

00:07:47.710 --> 00:07:49.100
For example, on one thread,

00:07:49.100 --> 00:07:51.490
the poster announced that he
was about to take his own life.

00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:53.280
One response to this was:

00:07:53.280 --> 00:07:54.290
"If you change your mind,"

00:07:54.290 --> 00:07:55.690
"call help ASAP"

00:07:56.020 --> 00:07:57.200
However, the person who said this

00:07:57.200 --> 00:07:59.790
was then chastised by
another user who replied:

00:08:00.090 --> 00:08:01.670
"Why would you say <b>THAT</b> here?"

00:08:02.030 --> 00:08:03.480
This last comment was then liked

00:08:03.480 --> 00:08:05.300
by the site administrator,
by the way.

00:08:05.300 --> 00:08:07.750
Their most important
policy relates to age.

00:08:07.750 --> 00:08:10.590
The site states that you must
be 18 or over to sign up.

00:08:10.910 --> 00:08:12.540
Their method of enforcing this?

00:08:12.540 --> 00:08:13.410
A tickbox

00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:16.150
that you have to check to
verify that you are actually 18.

00:08:16.150 --> 00:08:17.620
No protections of any kind.

00:08:17.800 --> 00:08:20.100
There are a few more examples
of policies like this,

00:08:20.100 --> 00:08:21.820
some of which I'm going
to go through later,

00:08:21.820 --> 00:08:23.510
but what's important
to note now is that

00:08:23.510 --> 00:08:25.410
they're not enforced
in any meaningful way.

00:08:25.700 --> 00:08:26.760
I later learned that

00:08:26.760 --> 00:08:28.670
most of them were actually
added not too long ago

00:08:28.670 --> 00:08:30.860
when the site began coming
under more scrutiny,

00:08:30.860 --> 00:08:32.660
so it's a nice covering exercise.

00:08:33.010 --> 00:08:35.610
Earlier iterations of the
site were much more blatant.

00:08:35.800 --> 00:08:37.170
And this led me to wonder:

00:08:37.170 --> 00:08:38.720
If you peel away the veneer,

00:08:38.720 --> 00:08:41.500
what's the actual belief system
underpinning this site?

00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:43.390
And that's when I began
to uncover a hole

00:08:43.390 --> 00:08:45.160
so deep and so toxic,

00:08:45.160 --> 00:08:46.470
it just beggars belief.

00:08:47.010 --> 00:08:49.220
Let's start with the
site's real philosophy.

00:08:49.220 --> 00:08:51.850
In a prominent sticky thread
at the top of the forum page,

00:08:51.850 --> 00:08:53.450
there's a list of four philosophies

00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:55.110
that the admins describe as being

00:08:55.110 --> 00:08:56.620
"adjacent" to theirs.

00:08:56.890 --> 00:08:58.840
This is key to understanding
their mindset.

00:08:59.100 --> 00:08:59.900
There's...

00:08:59.900 --> 00:09:00.560
(drumroll...)

00:09:00.560 --> 00:09:01.480
nihilism,

00:09:01.480 --> 00:09:03.230
which they reductively summarize as:

00:09:03.230 --> 00:09:05.850
"A philosophy that views
all life as meaningless"

00:09:06.160 --> 00:09:07.440
We'll just leave that one as is.

00:09:07.660 --> 00:09:09.180
The second philosophy is

00:09:09.180 --> 00:09:10.620
antinatalism,

00:09:10.620 --> 00:09:11.800
which they describe as:

00:09:11.800 --> 00:09:14.850
"A philosophy that assigns
negative value to existence..."

00:09:14.850 --> 00:09:18.500
"(because existence) is imposed upon
the individual without their consent."

00:09:18.780 --> 00:09:20.220
Now, in recent years,

00:09:20.220 --> 00:09:23.260
this particular idea has gained
traction on various forums.

00:09:23.260 --> 00:09:25.790
I don't want to get diverted
by the subculture too much.

00:09:25.990 --> 00:09:27.230
Whatever its origins,

00:09:27.230 --> 00:09:29.200
its main idea now amounts to a

00:09:29.200 --> 00:09:31.810
serious resentment of
one's parents, because

00:09:31.810 --> 00:09:33.650
they're the ones who
put you on this planet,

00:09:33.650 --> 00:09:35.420
and they did that to
satisfy their own

00:09:35.420 --> 00:09:37.140
selfish requirements
to have children.

00:09:37.500 --> 00:09:38.940
Here's an example of how this idea

00:09:38.940 --> 00:09:41.090
manifests in conversations
on the forum.

00:09:41.300 --> 00:09:42.080
In one thread,

00:09:42.080 --> 00:09:43.740
a user describes how
he's worried about

00:09:43.740 --> 00:09:46.080
the pain he’d cause to his
mother if he took his own life.

00:09:46.580 --> 00:09:48.120
To which another user replies:

00:09:48.820 --> 00:09:51.320
"I'm always curious how
people who want to CTB"

00:09:51.320 --> 00:09:52.910
"can still love their
mother so much."

00:09:52.910 --> 00:09:53.760
"After all,"

00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:56.130
"they used you as a meat
shield for their own good."

00:09:56.610 --> 00:09:58.080
The third philosophy is

00:09:58.080 --> 00:09:59.380
promortalism,

00:09:59.840 --> 00:10:00.680
described as:

00:10:00.680 --> 00:10:03.370
"A philosophy that assigns
a positive value to death"

00:10:03.630 --> 00:10:04.960
Now, this one is so stupid,

00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:06.440
it's tempting to skip over,

00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:08.250
but it's actually really important.

00:10:08.250 --> 00:10:10.950
It underpins an attitude that you
encounter on the forum constantly:

00:10:11.190 --> 00:10:13.010
the idea that life is so horrible

00:10:13.010 --> 00:10:15.010
it's amoral to act in
any way that might

00:10:15.010 --> 00:10:16.810
dissuade someone from
ending their life.

00:10:17.170 --> 00:10:18.880
In practice, it's used constantly

00:10:18.880 --> 00:10:20.950
to chastise those who
recommend therapy,

00:10:20.950 --> 00:10:23.260
or to suggest that there
might be a reason to live.

00:10:23.260 --> 00:10:24.800
In fact, on this forum,

00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:26.120
suggesting there's a reason to live

00:10:26.120 --> 00:10:28.270
is about the most gauche
thing you could possibly say.

00:10:28.660 --> 00:10:29.390
And last,

00:10:29.990 --> 00:10:30.930
(and least)

00:10:31.290 --> 00:10:32.640
libertarianism.

00:10:32.640 --> 00:10:35.150
"The belief that the individual
is the owner of their own body"

00:10:35.150 --> 00:10:37.760
"and has the right to dispose
of it however they see fit."

00:10:38.090 --> 00:10:38.710
Um...

00:10:38.710 --> 00:10:40.960
It wouldn't be my go-to
summary of libertarianism.

00:10:41.210 --> 00:10:42.310
Uh, there's obviously some kind of

00:10:42.310 --> 00:10:44.190
'personal freedom' connection
being made here,

00:10:44.190 --> 00:10:46.210
for those who might already
be in that headspace,

00:10:46.910 --> 00:10:47.510
I don't know.

00:10:47.510 --> 00:10:48.490
Feels a bit tacked on.

00:10:48.640 --> 00:10:50.780
Now, along with this is the
forum's attitude towards

00:10:50.780 --> 00:10:52.620
all mental health
and recovery services.

00:10:53.240 --> 00:10:55.300
In a nutshell, if you're
thinking of ending your life,

00:10:55.300 --> 00:10:56.800
the predominant opinion on the forum

00:10:56.800 --> 00:10:59.340
is that you should not speak
to anyone about your thoughts,

00:10:59.340 --> 00:11:00.420
because if you do,

00:11:00.420 --> 00:11:02.140
they're going to lock
you up in a psych ward.

00:11:02.390 --> 00:11:04.270
This isn't directly
expressed in the site's

00:11:04.270 --> 00:11:05.840
official link to recovery options,

00:11:05.840 --> 00:11:08.420
where, at least, they provide
a few hotline numbers

00:11:08.420 --> 00:11:09.360
as well as

00:11:09.360 --> 00:11:11.380
zany pseudoscience alternatives like

00:11:11.380 --> 00:11:13.200
microdosing LSD and

00:11:13.200 --> 00:11:15.070
MDMA-assisted therapy.

00:11:15.300 --> 00:11:17.880
No, if you want to get a sense
of what the admins approve of,

00:11:17.880 --> 00:11:19.330
just look at their moderation.

00:11:19.330 --> 00:11:20.220
What they permit

00:11:20.220 --> 00:11:22.500
and what many of the
most prolific members say.

00:11:22.980 --> 00:11:23.720
For example,

00:11:23.720 --> 00:11:24.910
when one user posted:

00:11:25.270 --> 00:11:26.180
"I learned long ago that there's"

00:11:26.180 --> 00:11:28.290
"absolutely no point
in talking to people."

00:11:28.290 --> 00:11:29.680
"Doctors, psychiatrists,"

00:11:29.680 --> 00:11:30.690
"family, friends,"

00:11:30.690 --> 00:11:31.620
"it doesn't matter,"

00:11:31.620 --> 00:11:32.630
"they never listen..."

00:11:32.630 --> 00:11:34.530
"they seem to prefer
taking others hostage"

00:11:34.530 --> 00:11:37.030
"over respecting someone's
decision to CTB."

00:11:37.380 --> 00:11:38.530
In response to this,

00:11:38.530 --> 00:11:40.110
one of the most prolific members,

00:11:40.110 --> 00:11:42.780
who's posted over 16,000
messages on this site,

00:11:42.780 --> 00:11:43.640
responded:

00:11:43.900 --> 00:11:44.870
"I agree with this."

00:11:44.870 --> 00:11:46.790
"People will never be
able to understand"

00:11:46.790 --> 00:11:48.620
"as they are not in
a similar situation"

00:11:48.620 --> 00:11:50.170
"and if you open up
about your suffering"

00:11:50.170 --> 00:11:52.560
"it's likely that you will just
get invalidated in some way."

00:11:52.970 --> 00:11:54.230
I'll get back to this member,

00:11:54.230 --> 00:11:57.020
who I'll refer to as 'cake123' later.

00:11:57.230 --> 00:11:59.040
It really only takes
a few minutes of

00:11:59.040 --> 00:12:01.380
viewing various posts
on their responses

00:12:01.380 --> 00:12:03.200
for you to become exposed to this

00:12:03.200 --> 00:12:04.670
anti-help perspective,

00:12:04.670 --> 00:12:05.940
and only a few hours more

00:12:05.940 --> 00:12:07.680
for it to become
crystallized in your mind.

00:12:07.980 --> 00:12:10.050
I understood it perfectly
well before I discovered

00:12:10.050 --> 00:12:11.970
their four ‘adjacent’ philosophies.

00:12:12.340 --> 00:12:14.510
So, are all the members
of the site like this?

00:12:14.510 --> 00:12:15.100
No.

00:12:15.100 --> 00:12:17.520
There are some who strongly
disagree with this mindset.

00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:19.080
Some who do call it toxic.

00:12:19.470 --> 00:12:21.280
The moderator's response
to this criticism

00:12:21.280 --> 00:12:22.890
is nearly always to emphasize that

00:12:22.890 --> 00:12:24.580
free speech is of greater importance.

00:12:24.930 --> 00:12:26.270
The 'free speech' argument is,

00:12:26.270 --> 00:12:28.070
again, another smokescreen.

00:12:28.070 --> 00:12:30.280
It allows the moderators
to promote and encourage

00:12:30.280 --> 00:12:31.930
seriously dangerous conversations,

00:12:31.930 --> 00:12:34.430
while quietly banning those
who protested too much.

00:12:34.680 --> 00:12:35.750
"I need to CTB"

00:12:35.750 --> 00:12:36.990
"but I don't have a method."

00:12:36.990 --> 00:12:38.820
"[Method A] is just unavailable."

00:12:38.820 --> 00:12:41.240
"I've tried so hard with it
but it's never worked out."

00:12:41.470 --> 00:12:43.440
"[Method B], [Method C]
and [Method D]"

00:12:43.440 --> 00:12:45.830
"are all unbelievably difficult
to get your hands on."

00:12:46.120 --> 00:12:48.580
"Everything else is too
painful, slow or unreliable."

00:12:48.830 --> 00:12:49.920
"This isn't fair."

00:12:49.920 --> 00:12:51.360
"I truly hate it here."

00:12:52.170 --> 00:12:53.750
"If you really want to
leave this world,"

00:12:53.750 --> 00:12:55.100
"the method will find you."

00:12:55.100 --> 00:12:56.350
"And you will not fail."

00:12:56.510 --> 00:12:57.530
"Try [Method E]."

00:12:57.530 --> 00:12:58.420
"All you need..."

00:12:58.640 --> 00:13:00.220
And then this is followed
with instructions

00:13:00.220 --> 00:13:02.340
and a video to give
more concrete specifics.

00:13:02.770 --> 00:13:03.850
Free speech, indeed.

00:13:04.240 --> 00:13:05.930
Free speech that
directly contradicts

00:13:05.930 --> 00:13:09.520
the supposed core policy of not
suggesting, helping or encouraging.

00:13:09.870 --> 00:13:11.460
This is what SS

00:13:11.460 --> 00:13:12.560
actually is.

00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:15.320
And this pretense of valuing
free speech above all else

00:13:15.320 --> 00:13:17.340
is persuasive to many on the forum,

00:13:17.340 --> 00:13:18.990
but what a lot of them don't realize

00:13:18.990 --> 00:13:20.570
is that regardless of their views,

00:13:20.570 --> 00:13:22.390
they're participating
in a percentage game.

00:13:22.760 --> 00:13:23.510
As I mentioned,

00:13:23.510 --> 00:13:25.440
the site gets millions
of page views a month.

00:13:25.650 --> 00:13:26.770
And of those who sign up,

00:13:26.770 --> 00:13:28.790
a significant portion
are clearly attracted

00:13:28.790 --> 00:13:30.250
to the most extreme ideas.

00:13:30.630 --> 00:13:31.590
That's the problem.

00:13:31.590 --> 00:13:33.210
The fact that some members
have the freedom

00:13:33.210 --> 00:13:35.780
to call these ideas toxic
without getting banned

00:13:35.780 --> 00:13:37.560
doesn't make that problem any better.

00:13:37.560 --> 00:13:39.140
The stakes are just too high.

00:13:39.140 --> 00:13:42.000
When a minor is assisted in
ending their life on the forum,

00:13:42.000 --> 00:13:44.500
that's not the unfortunate
price of free speech,

00:13:44.500 --> 00:13:46.870
that's a catastrophic
moderation failure.

00:13:47.180 --> 00:13:48.440
Now, the death of Bobby C

00:13:48.440 --> 00:13:50.300
is a perfect example of this failure.

00:13:50.520 --> 00:13:52.160
You see, months before he died,

00:13:52.160 --> 00:13:54.180
he had been planning how he
was going to end his life

00:13:54.180 --> 00:13:56.030
with the help of others on the site.

00:13:56.360 --> 00:13:57.680
First, let me show you

00:13:57.680 --> 00:13:58.800
how the scaremongering

00:13:58.800 --> 00:14:00.960
and blatant misinformation
about seeking help

00:14:00.960 --> 00:14:02.110
influenced his thinking:

00:14:02.540 --> 00:14:04.750
"What are the consequences
of failing to CTB?"

00:14:05.060 --> 00:14:07.100
"I don't have a therapist
or anything like that."

00:14:07.100 --> 00:14:08.990
"I'm considered 'normal'
by most people."

00:14:09.170 --> 00:14:10.500
"However, I absolutely"

00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:12.990
"do not want to risk
hospitalisation if I fail."

00:14:12.990 --> 00:14:15.470
"I'm scared to reach out to
any therapist or help service"

00:14:15.470 --> 00:14:17.300
"in case they force
me into a hospital"

00:14:17.300 --> 00:14:20.060
"because they'll completely
prevent my attempts to CTB."

00:14:20.400 --> 00:14:22.680
Now, this is the
reddest of red flags,

00:14:22.680 --> 00:14:24.160
because he's just admitted that

00:14:24.160 --> 00:14:25.790
he's never sought help ever.

00:14:25.790 --> 00:14:26.940
But the first response?

00:14:27.460 --> 00:14:29.270
"Your biggest consequence
is going to be either"

00:14:29.270 --> 00:14:30.250
"permanent damage"

00:14:30.250 --> 00:14:31.360
"or hospitalisation."

00:14:31.360 --> 00:14:33.610
"Both can be avoided with
enough research and planning."

00:14:34.070 --> 00:14:34.900
There is at least

00:14:34.900 --> 00:14:36.750
one message that advises caution:

00:14:36.950 --> 00:14:38.850
"If there's a part of you
that wants to get help,"

00:14:38.850 --> 00:14:39.560
"seek it."

00:14:39.560 --> 00:14:42.220
"Don't make a permanent decision
if you're not entirely sure."

00:14:42.220 --> 00:14:43.970
"There are people you can talk to"

00:14:43.970 --> 00:14:45.840
"who won't automatically
hospitalise you..."

00:14:45.840 --> 00:14:47.410
However, the person who said this

00:14:47.410 --> 00:14:48.740
then felt it pertinent to

00:14:48.740 --> 00:14:50.420
'balance' this statement

00:14:50.420 --> 00:14:52.290
by describing how
terrible and uncaring

00:14:52.290 --> 00:14:54.360
the mental health services
in their country are.

00:14:54.900 --> 00:14:56.810
And that there was the sole instance

00:14:56.810 --> 00:14:58.660
where someone suggested to Bobby C

00:14:58.660 --> 00:15:00.450
that he might reconsider his plans.

00:15:00.450 --> 00:15:01.760
It had been mentioned once,

00:15:01.760 --> 00:15:02.830
and once was enough.

00:15:03.050 --> 00:15:05.210
The rest of the comments
are all encouragement

00:15:05.210 --> 00:15:06.640
along with a large dose of

00:15:06.640 --> 00:15:08.840
anti-therapy and anti-help dogma.

00:15:09.080 --> 00:15:11.440
Unfortunately, Bobby C
was much more convinced

00:15:11.440 --> 00:15:13.630
by the suggestion that
he should plan properly,

00:15:13.990 --> 00:15:14.830
so he did.

00:15:15.140 --> 00:15:16.770
There's a whole other
thread where he,

00:15:16.770 --> 00:15:18.220
assisted by a few others,

00:15:18.220 --> 00:15:20.010
assessed the best approach
he should take

00:15:20.010 --> 00:15:21.730
to carrying through
his chosen method.

00:15:21.730 --> 00:15:23.890
Again, I'm not going to
detail the method he used.

00:15:24.140 --> 00:15:25.220
The only thing I'll say

00:15:25.220 --> 00:15:26.990
is that I found it
unbelievably shocking

00:15:26.990 --> 00:15:28.270
due to how violent it was.

00:15:28.640 --> 00:15:30.570
It has honestly stuck
with me ever since.

00:15:31.030 --> 00:15:32.790
The reaction on the
forum was more like

00:15:32.790 --> 00:15:33.560
admiration.

00:15:33.730 --> 00:15:35.100
As one commenter put it:

00:15:35.330 --> 00:15:37.400
"...you got BALLS to
choose this method."

00:15:37.400 --> 00:15:37.950
For me,

00:15:37.950 --> 00:15:39.600
the most upsetting thing
about this site

00:15:39.600 --> 00:15:41.080
are the ‘Goodbye’ threads.

00:15:41.390 --> 00:15:42.770
The first page I ever saw,

00:15:42.770 --> 00:15:43.960
the one by Bobby C,

00:15:43.960 --> 00:15:45.010
was a goodbye thread.

00:15:45.300 --> 00:15:46.140
As you can imagine,

00:15:46.140 --> 00:15:47.910
goodbye threads are posted by users

00:15:47.910 --> 00:15:50.140
who are ready to carry
through their final plans.

00:15:50.450 --> 00:15:52.470
They're avoided by many
people on the site

00:15:52.470 --> 00:15:53.940
who find them too upsetting.

00:15:54.230 --> 00:15:56.020
What's particularly
notable about them

00:15:56.020 --> 00:15:58.090
is that you don't often
see anyone make an appeal

00:15:58.090 --> 00:16:00.170
for the original poster
to reconsider,

00:16:00.170 --> 00:16:02.180
(they're called 'goodbye'
threads for a reason)

00:16:02.180 --> 00:16:04.450
because, in the logic
of this community,

00:16:04.450 --> 00:16:05.740
the point of no return has been

00:16:05.740 --> 00:16:07.240
well and truly passed.

00:16:07.240 --> 00:16:08.730
And on every one of these threads,

00:16:08.730 --> 00:16:10.580
every single one that I've read,

00:16:10.580 --> 00:16:12.670
the same prolific toxic member

00:16:12.670 --> 00:16:13.840
I mentioned earlier,

00:16:13.840 --> 00:16:15.080
cake123,

00:16:15.080 --> 00:16:17.620
will respond with the
variation on this line:

00:16:18.220 --> 00:16:18.980
"Farewell."

00:16:18.980 --> 00:16:21.090
"I hope that you find the
freedom from your suffering"

00:16:21.090 --> 00:16:22.090
"that you wish for."

00:16:22.520 --> 00:16:23.920
Now, it's not hard to see

00:16:23.920 --> 00:16:25.890
how all of this could
be described as a cult.

00:16:26.240 --> 00:16:27.780
There are three telltale signs:

00:16:28.170 --> 00:16:28.640
First,

00:16:28.640 --> 00:16:31.170
it has a highly peculiar
alternative ideology

00:16:31.170 --> 00:16:33.280
which runs contrary to
mainstream thinking.

00:16:33.280 --> 00:16:34.160
In particular,

00:16:34.160 --> 00:16:36.540
that inversion of morality
I spoke about earlier

00:16:36.540 --> 00:16:38.800
that you shouldn't stand in
the way of someone dying.

00:16:39.290 --> 00:16:39.810
Second,

00:16:39.810 --> 00:16:42.230
a ridiculous hostility to
mental health professionals

00:16:42.230 --> 00:16:43.870
and the idea of treatment.

00:16:44.110 --> 00:16:45.830
You see this a lot with Scientology.

00:16:45.830 --> 00:16:47.300
Their ideology runs contrary to

00:16:47.300 --> 00:16:49.100
mainstream mental health
treatment too,

00:16:49.100 --> 00:16:50.650
so they viciously attack it.

00:16:50.650 --> 00:16:51.980
It's Cult 101.

00:16:51.980 --> 00:16:53.520
Your ideology will seem stronger

00:16:53.520 --> 00:16:55.660
if you clobber all
competing ways of thinking.

00:16:55.660 --> 00:16:56.400
Third,

00:16:56.400 --> 00:16:58.070
and most telling for cults,

00:16:58.070 --> 00:16:59.540
including Scientology,

00:16:59.540 --> 00:17:01.950
cutting people off from
their support networks.

00:17:02.320 --> 00:17:04.010
Medical professionals
and therapists?

00:17:04.010 --> 00:17:05.380
Well, they only care about money,

00:17:05.380 --> 00:17:07.500
and they're going to lock you up if
you tell them what you're thinking.

00:17:07.910 --> 00:17:08.900
Your parents?

00:17:08.900 --> 00:17:10.560
They're the ones who did this
to you in the first place

00:17:10.560 --> 00:17:13.180
by selfishly dragging you
into this meaningless world.

00:17:13.450 --> 00:17:14.310
You can't trust them.

00:17:14.610 --> 00:17:16.680
And those preventing you
from harming yourself?

00:17:16.680 --> 00:17:17.990
They're assaulting your freedom

00:17:17.990 --> 00:17:19.540
to do what you want with your body.

00:17:19.950 --> 00:17:21.990
And in order to lock you
in as much as possible,

00:17:21.990 --> 00:17:24.630
it's always assumed that if
you register on the site,

00:17:24.630 --> 00:17:27.040
you must have exhausted
all other options.

00:17:27.040 --> 00:17:27.750
I mean,

00:17:27.750 --> 00:17:28.960
