site and those like it,

00:33:29.890 --> 00:33:31.210
because by doing so,

00:33:31.210 --> 00:33:33.870
they're providing vulnerable
people as well as minors

00:33:33.870 --> 00:33:36.730
with a direct link to instructions
to end their own lives.

00:33:37.050 --> 00:33:38.870
Yes, legally they can...

00:33:38.870 --> 00:33:39.800
but they shouldn't.

00:33:39.960 --> 00:33:41.730
And there's increasing
need for action.

00:33:41.730 --> 00:33:44.370
In the U.K., among
15 to 19 year olds,

00:33:44.370 --> 00:33:45.880
the rate of taking one's own life

00:33:45.880 --> 00:33:48.360
has sharply increased by 35%

00:33:48.360 --> 00:33:50.310
throughout 2020 and 2021.

00:33:50.730 --> 00:33:51.620
In the U.S.,

00:33:51.620 --> 00:33:52.890
the overall rate has increased

00:33:52.890 --> 00:33:55.580
also by 35% since 1999,

00:33:55.580 --> 00:33:58.000
with 15 to 24 year olds
being at higher risk

00:33:58.000 --> 00:33:59.380
than any other age group.

00:33:59.760 --> 00:34:00.840
Now, given these stats

00:34:00.840 --> 00:34:03.850
on how SS is crossing the
line in so many other ways,

00:34:03.850 --> 00:34:06.440
other attempts to halt
its activities are emerging.

00:34:06.700 --> 00:34:08.140
It's not illegal in most places

00:34:08.140 --> 00:34:10.030
to encourage others
to harm themselves.

00:34:10.500 --> 00:34:11.340
That, at present,

00:34:11.340 --> 00:34:13.390
broadly falls within the
boundaries of free speech

00:34:13.390 --> 00:34:14.790
in the U.S. and Europe.

00:34:14.790 --> 00:34:15.780
But in most countries,

00:34:15.780 --> 00:34:18.050
it is illegal to provide
instructions and help.

00:34:18.370 --> 00:34:19.390
So, with that in mind,

00:34:19.390 --> 00:34:21.630
in October 2022, in the U.S.,

00:34:21.630 --> 00:34:23.230
a new bipartisan bill called

00:34:23.230 --> 00:34:25.978
the Stop Online Assisted
S---cide Forums Act

00:34:25.980 --> 00:34:27.970
was introduced to the
House of Representatives

00:34:27.970 --> 00:34:29.850
