People are very often ashamed to

00:44:11.510 --> 00:44:14.280
discuss feelings of wanting to
end their own lives openly,

00:44:14.280 --> 00:44:16.660
which is a poor reflection
on society as a whole.

00:44:17.020 --> 00:44:18.250
Let's name one stigma

00:44:18.250 --> 00:44:20.150
mentioned by Professor
Rory O’Connor:

00:44:20.150 --> 00:44:22.210
it's way too commonly
to write it as a

00:44:22.210 --> 00:44:23.140
"selfish act",

00:44:23.500 --> 00:44:26.420
which in turn makes it far less
likely that people will bring it up

00:44:26.420 --> 00:44:28.380
for fear of being
chastised or shunned.

00:44:28.790 --> 00:44:29.850
Instead, he suggests,

00:44:30.080 --> 00:44:31.930
the act is way more
likely to be carried out

00:44:31.930 --> 00:44:33.390
in a moment of desperation

00:44:33.390 --> 00:44:34.570
by those in crisis,

00:44:34.570 --> 00:44:37.050
who could no longer withstand
severe mental pain,

00:44:37.050 --> 00:44:39.770
and who are unable to see
beyond that pain at that moment.

00:44:40.130 --> 00:44:41.570
For those feeling hopeless,

00:44:41.570 --> 00:44:42.850
you should speak to a few people

00:44:42.850 --> 00:44:44.400
before making any other plans.

00:44:44.850 --> 00:44:46.320
Those who say otherwise are probably

00:44:46.320 --> 00:44:47.890
not acting in your real interest.

00:44:48.240 --> 00:44:50.450
Now, I've put a couple of links
in the description below,

00:44:50.450 --> 00:44:53.350
but there may very easily be
local options you can access with

00:44:53.350 --> 00:44:55.240
a quick search engine
check, for example.

00:44:55.660 --> 00:44:56.590
And also, remember

00:44:56.590 --> 00:44:58.570
that if for some reason
you don't connect

00:44:58.570 --> 00:45:00.160
with one mental health specialist,

00:45:00.160 --> 00:45:02.250
this doesn't mean that
seeking help is pointless.

00:45:02.500 --> 00:45:04.660
If one person doesn't
succeed in helping you,

00:45:04.660 --> 00:45:06.050
someone else most likely can.

00:45:06.480 --> 00:45:08.020
And please don't go alone.

00:45:08.020 --> 00:45:09.490
Recovery is possible.

00:45:09.490 --> 00:45:10.560
Things can get better,

00:45:10.560 --> 00:45:12.850
and there are people in the world
who do want the best for you.

00:45:13.130 --> 00:45:14.720
And if you're feeling
like you're in crisis,

00:45:14.720 --> 00:45:16.350
there are experts who
can at least provide you

00:45:16.350 --> 00:45:17.900
with a better sense of your options.

00:45:18.310 --> 00:45:20.060
Nothing bad will come
from speaking to them.

00:45:20.290 --> 00:45:21.970
Again, see the links
in the description.

00:45:22.230 --> 00:45:23.620
And to everyone else watching,

00:45:23.620 --> 00:45:24.880
I have a final thought.

00:45:24.880 --> 00:45:26.790
There really should be
no reason a person has to

00:45:26.790 --> 00:45:29.080
seek out an anonymous forum
to find comfort.

00:45:29.500 --> 00:45:31.870
There are things we can all
do directly to combat this,

00:45:31.870 --> 00:45:33.980
by applying small
protocols of our own.

00:45:34.360 --> 00:45:36.210
Do we know people we
suspect are in pain?

00:45:36.480 --> 00:45:38.210
Can we just give them a
call and listen to them?

00:45:38.590 --> 00:45:39.840
Are there ways we can make the world

00:45:39.840 --> 00:45:41.780
a little nicer for them
and for others?

00:45:42.120 --> 00:45:43.410
And can we be a little
less aggressive

00:45:43.410 --> 00:45:46.030
when others do or say
things we find irritating?

00:45:46.330 --> 00:45:47.980
Can we just cut people's
slack sometimes?

00:45:47.980 --> 00:45:49.150
Because you never know,

00:45:49.150 --> 00:45:50.660
they could be having a
tough time right now

00:45:50.660 --> 00:45:52.270
due to problems that we can't see.

00:45:52.680 --> 00:45:54.400
This is the harder road
to take for sure,

00:45:54.400 --> 00:45:56.240
but it's also highly rewarding too.

00:45:56.240 --> 00:45:59.320
A report from the International
Association for S---cide Prevention

00:45:59.320 --> 00:46:00.160
put it best:

00:46:00.520 --> 00:46:02.640
"Every step closer can
connect someone to life"

00:46:02.640 --> 00:46:03.850
"and the help they want."

00:46:04.300 --> 00:46:05.810
"Sometimes those steps are big,"

00:46:06.250 --> 00:46:07.000
"but sometimes"

00:46:07.000 --> 00:46:08.460
"all it takes is a smile."

00:46:09.120 --> 00:46:10.290
That's everything I have to say.

00:46:10.670 --> 00:46:11.570
Thanks very much.

